        "username": "rassilon1963",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-05-07T20:10:25.192Z",
        "cooked": "<p>the link is this long to protect your privacy. it means Signal can’t get the group info even if they wanted. that is also the reason the group info isn’t fetched in most previews - Signal uses URL fragments precisely because they allow them to share info the server can’t see, but most previewers out there ignore URL fragments (which btw also often leads to issues when you link to a specific part of a page, for example with Wikipedia).<br>\nSignal could implement an in-app group details fetcher that is client-side only, but that won’t solve the issue for other apps. however since privacy and security are and always will be the first priority, i don’t see Signal changing the URLs in a way that leaks data any time soon.</p>",
